:INFO
Two Formats, One Unusual Novel
Lincoln in the Bardo has 166 distinct narrator voices, and Saunders distinguishes \
every one of them in the text using typographic cues and attribution. I read the \
print version first and found it dazzling but occasionally difficult to track. \
The audio version, performed by over 160 readers, is a different experience \
entirely. It is not better or worse. It is genuinely another way of encountering \
the same novel, and I think it is worth trying both if the book interests you.

